= Non-Functional Requirements =

(% class="box infomessage" %)
(((
**FactHarbor targets high performance, production-grade security, and radical transparency.**
Our system attributes include sub-30s processing latency, encrypted storage, and auditable open-source logic.

🔗 **Project Repository:** [[FactHarbor on GitHub>>https://github.com/robertschaub/FactHarbor]]
)))

== 1. Technical Performance ==
* **Latency**: Analysis pipeline must complete in < 30 seconds.
* **Availability**: 99.0% uptime for core API and search.
* **Scalability**: Support for 1M+ claims and 100k+ concurrent users.

== 2. Transparency & Auditability ==
* **Open Source**: All analysis algorithms and prompts are public.
* **UCM Audit**: Every job is linked to a versioned configuration snapshot.
* **Public Metrics**: Error rates and source reliability distributions are public.

== 3. Security & Privacy ==
* **GDPR Compliance**: Full support for data export and account deletion.
* **Encryption**: AES-256 for data at rest; TLS 1.3 for data in transit.
* **Sanitization**: Strict input validation and HTML/JS scrubbing for all submissions.

== 4. Maintainability ==
* **Modularity**: Separation of AKEL (Logic) and persistence (.NET API).
* **Testability**: Mandatory Vitest coverage for all analysis modules.

